In this thesis, I am focusing on the applications which include only a single
 RFID reader and dense RFID tag populations.
 The main motivation of this thesis is to minimize the total identification
 time for a dense and passive RFID networks.
 Therefore, in this thesis, there are different proposals to solve the tag
 collision problem by enhancing the existing anti-collision protocols taking
 into consideration the physical layer parameters.
 Moreover, the applications of the dense RFID networks are following the
 EPCglobal C1 G2 standards 
